{"by":"Hendrikto","id":47763692,"kids":[47763795],"parent":47762864,"text":"&gt; My first troubling discovery was in 2025, when I made several errors then did a push -f to GitHub and blew away the git history for a half decade old repo. No data was lost, but the log of changes was.<p>I know this is besides the point somewhat, but: Learn your tools people. The commit history could probably have been easily restored without involving any backup. The commits are not just instantly gone.","time":1776162309,"type":"comment"}